<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-1051 </DOCNO><TEXT>This article is an interview with Louis Rene Beres. He gives his viewson such issues as: the ways current U.S. nuclear strategy contributeto the nuclear arms race and the danger of nuclear war, how to respondto strategic experts who argue that weapons are needed to make deterrencemore credible, the Reagan administration's argument that the U.S. mustmatch the Soviet Union's first strike capability to keep the Sovietsfrom getting the upper hand, and how the nuclear danger can be kept undercontrol.</TEXT></DOC>